Computer Science Agent)\n- **Role**: Computer Science Expert and Career Mentor\n- **Focus**: 2.master/2.1mcs in ONE project\n- **Responsibilities**: CS certifications, technical interviews, career development\n- **Workspace**: /Users/hope/.openclaw/agents/mcs/workspace\n- **Configuration**: Added to openclaw.json agents list\n- **Files created**: IDENTITY.md, USER.md, MEMORY.md\n\n### Career Development Analysis\n- **Career trajectory**: Wensi (13w) → Yuxin (30w) → Suyin (48w) → Ant Group\n- **Certifications**: 6 achieved, IELTS/MBA/FRM in progress\n- **AI Research Goal**: Publish in top-tier journals (NeurIPS, ICML, IEEE TPAMI)\n- **Recommended focus**: Financial AI, explainable AI, federated learning\n- **Study timeline**: 18-24 months for first publication\n\n### Memory System Evaluation - Mem0\n- **Mem0 features**: Hybrid datastore (graph + vector + key-value), automatic memory extraction, enterprise-grade security\n- **Comparison**: Current file-based system vs Mem0 cloud service\n- **Recommendation**: Continue with local file system for privacy, consider Mem0 OSS for future self-hosted deployment\n- **Key advantage of Mem0**: Cross-agent memory sharing and semantic search capabilities\n\n### Heartbeat Task Enhancement\n- **Problem identified**: Hourly heartbeats generating redundant content in daily logs\n- **Solution implemented**: Restrict heartbeat to health checks only, reduce frequency to every 2 hours\n- **New schedule**: 8:00, 10:00, 12:00, 14:00, 16:00, 18:00, 20:00 (silent 22:00-8:00)\n- **Scope limitation**: Only verify agent health status, no detailed reports or log writing\n- **Benefits**: Eliminates redundant memory entries, reduces system load by 50%\n\n### Shared Memory System Removal\n- **Problem identified**: Shared memory directory created unnecessary complexity\n- **Solution implemented**: Completely removed /Users/hope/.openclaw/shared/ directory\n- **New protocol**: Direct query model - Main Agent queries sub-agents directly when needed\n-